# Case D: Roster Export Automation

## Client
Mr. Ring

## Problem
Canvas LMS lacks a clean one-click export for class rosters. Current exports are messy CSVs requiring manual cleanup.

## Goal
A frictionless tool that exports a formatted class roster from Canvas directly into a clean Google Sheet or Doc, handling multi-section classes correctly.

## Tech Stack
To be decided in discovery (Python + Canvas API OR Chrome extension reading the Canvas page directly). Leaning toward Canvas API approach.

## Team
Developers: James Lake, Magnus Songhurst
Club Lead: Cayden Auyang

## Working Rules
- This folder is scoped to Case D only. Do not modify files outside projects/case-d-roster-export/ unless explicitly asked.
- Do not commit secrets, API keys, or credentials. Use .env files and add them to .gitignore.
- Follow the club branch naming convention: case-d/short-description (lowercase, hyphens).
- Never push directly to main. All changes go through a Pull Request with at least 1 approval.
- When writing code, prefer clarity over cleverness. These developers are high school students learning collaborative coding.
- If you generate code the developer cannot explain, flag it and summarize what it does in plain English.

## Definition of Done (Phase 1)
Architectural decision made (API vs extension), then a working prototype that exports one class roster cleanly into a Google Sheet.
